DAMATURU – Yobe State House of Assembly aspirant for Fika East constituency on the platform of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Musa Yusuf Maluri (Marafan Maluri), has assured his constituents of effective representation if given the mandate come 2023 general election. Maluri made the pledge at the weekend during an interview with Daily Independent during his consultation with delegates, various stakeholders, leaders, women/youth groups of his Constituency. He expressed his gratitude to his supporters for their encouragement and support, noting that ‘Putting People First’ will continue to be his Slogan. -Advertisement- The hopeful lawmaker, who hails from the Maluri Ward of Fika Local Government Area, stated that if given the opportunity to serve, he will passionately represent the interest of the good people of Fika local government area, promising that “he would not let them down.” While commending the developmental strides of Governor Mai Mala Buni, on the restoration of peaceful coexistence, reconstruction and resettlement efforts, as well as infrastructural developments of the State, Maluri promised to work hand-in-hand with the Governor if elected; to ensure continued collaboration between the executive and legislative arms of the government. Maluri further said, his mission “is to give a formidable representation for the good people of Fika at the state assembly with a view to attracting developmental projects and promoting youth empowerment, reducing unemployment and guaranteeing adequate human and capital development in the constituency through improved agricultural production techniques.”